This paper discusses the h-index and its modifications, which are commonly used to measure the impact of scientific research. The h-index is widely used in computer science, particularly in subfields such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
